President Donald Trump recently visited Israel, where he met with President Reuven Rivlin and Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu. Trump expressed his commitment to achieving peace in the region and strengthening the relationship between the United States and Israel. He became the first sitting US President to visit the Western Wall and laid a wreath at Yad Vashem in memory of the Holocaust victims. Trump also met with Palestinian Authority President Mahmoud Abbas in Bethlehem, where he reiterated his commitment to achieving a peace agreement between Israelis and Palestinians.